"Wu W.B., Zhao Z.","Inference of trends in time series",2007,"Journal of the Royal Statistical Society. Series B: Statistical Methodology","69","3",,"391","410",,,10.1111/j.1467-9868.2007.00594.x,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-34249038957&partnerID=40&md5=fa77eb4e8a741e061bd588c3ea704ce0","University of Chicago, United States; Department of Statistics, University of Chicago, 5734 South University Avenue, Chicago, IL 60637, United States","Wu, W.B., University of Chicago, United States, Department of Statistics, University of Chicago, 5734 South University Avenue, Chicago, IL 60637, United States; Zhao, Z., University of Chicago, United States","We consider statistical inference of trends in mean non-stationary models. A test statistic is proposed for the existence of structural breaks in trends. On the basis of a strong invariance principle of stationary processes, we construct simultaneous confidence bands with asymptotically correct nominal coverage probabilities. The results are applied to global warming temperature data and Nile river flow data. Our confidence band of the trend of the global warming temperature series supports the claim that the trend is increasing over the last 150 years. © 2007 Royal Statistical Society.","Confidence bands; Global warming; Invariance principle; Non-linear time series; Non-parametric regression",,,,,,,"Andel, J., Netuka, I., Svara, K., On threshold autoregressive processes (1984) Kybernetika, 20, pp. 89-106; Bickel, P.J., Rosenblatt, M., On some global measures of the deviations of density function estimates (1973) Ann. Statist., 1, pp. 1071-1095; Bloomfield, P., Nychka, D., Climate spectra and detecting climate change (1992) Clim. Change, 21, pp. 275-287; Bühlmann, P., Sieve bootstrap for smoothing in nonstationary time series (1998) Ann. Statist., 26, pp. 48-83; Bühlmann, P., Bootstraps for time series (2002) Statist. Sci., 17, pp. 52-72; Carlstein, E., The use of subseries values for estimating the varia